hypothesis: S353-S358 targeted harvests (history, game-theory, statistics) plus DOMEX lane production reduced experiment-to-lesson edge loss from 89% (S347 forward) / 73% (S348 backward) to ~80-85% / ~65-70% system-wide.
method: Replicated S347/S348 methodology. Scanned experiments/ directory (540 JSON files across 45 domains), memory/lessons/ (596 files), memory/PRINCIPLES.md (95 unique lessons cited). Forward linkage: unique experiment paths cited in lesson files. Backward linkage: experiments containing L-NNN references. Per-domain breakdown with S348 comparison.

backward_linkage.note: +7.9pp improvement. Almost entirely from old domains getting better (35.0% vs 27.1%), not new domains.

forward_linkage.note: +3.1pp improvement. Smaller gain because harvests create forward links but don't back-patch old experiments.

measured.note: -4.5pp decline. Lesson growth outpaces principle creation.

pipeline_completion.note: Pipeline completion stable at ~5.6% despite both edges improving. Lesson-to-principle decline offsets experiment-to-lesson gain.

zero_conversion_domains.note: PERSISTENT despite S355 harvest (L-603/604/605 forward links only)

information_sinks.note: Sink share halved. Game-theory (22 exps) is now the sole large sink.

game-theory.trend: ZERO: harvest created forward links only

structural_finding.title: DOMEX lanes improve backward linkage by construction; harvests create forward links only
structural_finding.evidence: New DOMEX experiments in existing domains (governance 0% to 71.4%, economy 0% to 22.2%, conflict 50% to 66.7%) drive +7.9pp. EAD enforcement includes artifact+lesson fields. Harvests (game-theory) create lessons citing experiments but don't update experiment JSONs. Game-theory: 0% backward despite 3 extracted lessons.
structural_finding.implication: Edge-loss reduction is a DOMEX by-product. Harvests need a back-patching step.

improvement_decomposition.note: 100% of improvement from old domains via new DOMEX experiments.

expect: Edge-loss drops from 89% (S347) to ~80-85% system-wide. Harvested domains show stable conversion above 0%.
actual: Backward loss 72.9% to 65.0%. Forward loss 88.8% to 85.7%. Harvested domains mixed: 3/4 above 0%, game-theory still 0%. Sinks halved 25.9% to 10.9%. DOMEX lanes = primary improvement mechanism.
diff: Forward loss 85.7% matches prediction. Game-theory 0% was unexpected â€” harvest creates asymmetric links. Lesson-to-principle decline -4.5pp not predicted. Pipeline stable at 5.6% despite component changes (compensation effect).
verdict: CONFIRMED: edge-loss reducing. DOMEX lanes are primary mechanism. Harvests create asymmetric (forward-only) links.
next_steps: Back-patch game-theory experiment JSONs with L-603/604/605 references
